File: Flight Centre had previously said the ban will last until a time where SAA obtains certainty in the market. JOHANNESBURG - International travel agency Flight Centre Travel Group says it is lifting its "stop-sell" on SAA immediately.
In November last year, the cash-strapped airline failed to pay staff full salaries. SAA said it almost had no cash left after a strike. READ: Flight Centre clips SAA's wings As a result, the travel group announced it would no longer cover SAA tickets against its insolvency. Flight Centre had previously said the ban will last until a time where SAA obtains certainty in the market.